<paragraph blockId="10.[212,311,1125,1149]" box="[212,311,1125,1149]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2561">
<emphasis box="[212,311,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2561">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,1172,1164,1316]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2561">
This species was reported as a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[762,832,1164,1188]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="2561">China</collectingCountry>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[907,1089,1164,1188]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="10" pageNumber="2561">Hubei Province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yang T" pageId="10" pageNumber="2561" pagination="186 - 189" refId="ref6619" refString="Yang T. 2007. Tardigrades from some mosses of Shennong frame state forest parking in China. Acta Zootaxon Sin. 32 (1): 186 - 189." type="journal article" year="2007">Yang 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The eggs are spherical, with truncated cone-like projections, the shell is irregularly punctated. My specimens fit the description of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramazzotti G &amp; Maucci W" pageId="10" pageNumber="2561" pagination="1 - 1012" refId="ref6447" refString="Ramazzotti G, Maucci W. 1983. Il phylum tardigrada. Mem Ist Ital Idrobiol. 41: 1 - 1012." type="journal article" year="1983">Ramazzotti and Maucci 1983</bibRefCitation>
). It is the first report of this species from the Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau.
</paragraph>
